# Design Declaration

Before implementation, declare the design intent in one compact block:

- Governing rules used (at minimum `01-system-design`, `02-quality-gates`, `03-goal-loop`, `04-milestone-driven-delivery`, `08-issue-first` when substantial).
- Bound issue #n and milestone M*n* when applicable.
- Target layer and adjacent contract (see `docs/specs/ARCHITECTURE.md`).
- Why the adjacent lower layer is insufficient (if adding mechanism code).
- Smallest sufficient abstraction chosen.

Verification hook:

- After implementation, confirm the change still respects the declared boundary.
- If the boundary moved, explain why and update the declaration.

For `.ngb` work, cite invariant ids (I1–I6) the change preserves or tightens.
